author: fielding
msg: Fixed problem with mod_cgi-generated internal redirects trying to read
the request message-body twice.  The owners of mod_fastcgi and mod_php
(and any other input-reading modules that might generate an internal
redirect) should check their code for the same problem.
Also removed the redundant check in should_client_block.
Submitted by: Archie Cobbs <archie@whistle.com>, Roy Fielding

author: fielding
msg: Reduced timeout on lingering close, removed possibility of a blocked
read causing the child to hang, and stopped logging of errors if
the socket is not connected (reset by client).  This might be only a
stopgap measure until we can rethink the accept logic.
Reviewed by: Jim Jagielski, Marc Slemko
